Intharacha, also spelled In Racha (, ), was a nephew of Borommarachathirat I and the former lord of Suphanburi. He secured the Ayutthayan throne for the Suphannaphum dynasty and reigned as the sixth king of the Ayutthaya Kingdom from 1408 to 1424.
Upon his death, his two elder sons engaged in single combat on elephants and were both killed, leaving the throne to their youngest brother.
